review 4:
4/5
It was overall an OK stay.
4 for location. It was located in a nice green surrounding with tranquil atmosphere.  I enjoyed the morning breeze. Unfortunately it was facing the west :)
4 for cleanliness of the gladak house. some termite started to eat up the wooden blocks.
3.5 for cleanliness of the natural spring water plunge pool. Water was crystal clear but the pool base was a bit full of dried leaves and some moss
3 for food. taste was standard and menus rather very limited with not so much of local Balinese dishes.
4 for services. Staffs were friendly and helpful. thanks!
3.5 for overall safety. pathway to the villa from the entrance shouldn't be made as ramp, it could be slippery during rainy season (time when moss will start to grow). All was good during my stay but it was too steep for a ramp way.
review 5:
Really beautiful place with a spectacular environment where you can enjoy and relax, either with your family, couple or alone. Great and healthy food, friendly and attentive staff, perfect natural pool temperature. Large and beautiful rooms well adapted to the environment. Perfect rice fields, fresh air and good energy to disconnect and reconnect.
I will come back obviously.

name: Hara Bali

review 1:
Dirty place, lot of dust, dead flys on the floor. Toilet and shower the worst condition!!!!! the room service use dirty, stinky mop to "clean" the area. The same mop for toilet, shower and room!! Dirty bed linen .
Air conditioning doesn't work !!!!!! The ovner admited she knew about the problem and didnt explain me why she didnt fix it before rental.
Not recommended !
